					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I caught that D-101 got it rectally because of the odd numbering pattern - I wondered &quot;Is there an easter egg here?&quot; and looked at it as a sort of bit pattern set. 100 got it in the mouth, 101 gets it in a different ingestion. Makes sense.<br /> Upvoted with disgust.</p> <p>Also:</p> <blockquote> <p>Water examined after rehydration of brine-dead specimens shows no abnormal traits.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p>brine-dead</p> </blockquote> <p>goddammit.</p> 
				 	]]>
